body:
A fairly significant refactor that decouples the generation of a build plan from creating an image. Both are defined via traits. The image creation is setup such that if we wanted to use [something other than docker](https://github.com/railwayapp/nixpacks/discussions/121), we could.

The plan generator takes an app and environment and produces a build plan.

```rust
pub trait PlanGenerator {
    fn generate_plan(&mut self, app: &App, environment: &Environment) -> Result<BuildPlan>;
}
```

A builder takes a build plan and creates an image

```rust
pub trait Builder {
    fn create_image(&self, app_source: &str, plan: &BuildPlan) -> Result<()>;
}
```

The main library functions only care about these traits and the code is quite a bit cleaner.

I've also cleaned up the generate plan tests with a little helper.

_Note: I think this helps quite a bit but very open to suggestions on other improvements we could make_.
